Package tools

Class FileLoad

java.lang.Object
tools.FileLoad
public class FileLoad extends Object
Handles the loading and validation of different types of files related to a booking system, including customer, concert, and booking files.

  • Method Details

    • PreloadUser

      public boolean PreloadUser(String[] args) throws IncorrectPasswordException, IOException, FileNotFoundException, NotFoundException
      Preloads user information based on command line arguments. This method initializes file paths and user information based on the mode (admin or customer).
      Parameters:
      args - Command line arguments providing user mode and file paths.
      Returns:
      True if the user is loaded correctly, False otherwise.
      Throws:
      IncorrectPasswordException - If the password provided is incorrect.
      IOException - If there is an issue reading a file.
      FileNotFoundException - If a specified file cannot be found.
      NotFoundException - If a required entity is not found in the files.

    • authenticateUser

      public void authenticateUser(String userID, String userPsw, String customerFilePath) throws IncorrectPasswordException, IOException, FileNotFoundException, NotFoundException
      Authenticates a user by verifying their ID and password against stored credentials.
      Parameters:
      userID - The user's ID.
      userPsw - The user's password.
      customerFilePath - The file path containing customer data.
      Throws:
      IncorrectPasswordException - If the password does not match the stored password.
      IOException - If there is an issue reading the file.
      FileNotFoundException - If the customer file cannot be found.
      NotFoundException - If the customer is not found in the file.

    • loadCustomerInfo

      public String loadCustomerInfo(String customerID) throws IOException, FileNotFoundException, InvalidLineException, InvalidFormatException
      Loads customer information from a file.
      Parameters:
      customerID - The ID of the customer to load.
      Returns:
      The name of the customer.
      Throws:
      IOException - If there is an issue reading the file.
      FileNotFoundException - If the customer file cannot be found.
      InvalidLineException - If a line in the file does not conform to the expected format.
      InvalidFormatException - If the data format is correct but not valid.

    • loadVenue

      public Venue loadVenue(String venueName, BookingDetails bookingDetails, String concertId) throws IOException, FileNotFoundException, InvalidLineException
      Loads venue details from a file and integrates them with a specific concert's booking details.
      Parameters:
      venueName - The name of the venue to load.
      bookingDetails - Booking details to be integrated with venue information.
      concertId - The ID of the concert for which venue details are being loaded.
      Returns:
      A Venue object with details loaded and integrated.
      Throws:
      IOException - If there is an issue reading the file.
      FileNotFoundException - If the venue file cannot be found.
      InvalidLineException - If a line in the file does not conform to the expected format.
